    "An edge A → B indicates that index A is compared with index B in previous literature Fig. 22Fig.",
    "2 Workflow of the projection-based index Figure 22Figure2illustrates the workflow of projection-based indexes.",
    "For a d-dimensional dataset X, a projection function f:R d → R is applied to project X to a set of 1-D values X = { f (x) | x ∈ X }.Then, X is sorted and sequentially stored such that a 1-D learned index (e.g., RMI or PGMIndex) can be constructed to fit the mapping from projected values to corresponding storage locations.",
